# ai-provisioning-engine · Architecture documentation

> Condensed from design/DESIGN.md. Sources: §1 Positioning and Boundaries, §2 List of Responsibilities, §3 Core Abstractions and Interfaces, §6 External Adaptation.
> Platform version v1.4.0 | Go + Gin + Cobra + Wire | assembly domain

---

## 1. Component positioning

`ai-provisioning-engine` is the second half of the OpenStrata assembly backbone: the deployment/provisioning engine. It consumes the AssemblyPlan produced by `ai-dependency-resolver`, implements the plan into **Helm Values ​​/ Compose / Operator configuration**, and applies it to the running environment through **ArgoCD or direct connection to Helm** to implement "incremental deployment, rolling update, zero downtime".

### Core Issues
Turn "a confirmed assembly plan" into "actual changes to the environment that are safe, observable, and rollable" - only the differences are moved, and running services are not restarted.

### Required
core. Stages one to three are driven by `aictl up` to drive Compose; the full file is driven by the boot portal + ArgoCD GitOps.

### Boundary demarcation

| Components | Relationships | Description |
|------|------|------|
| **ai-dependency-resolver** | Upstream | Resolver output Plan -> own repository consumption Plan, only execution, not counting dependencies |
| **ai-cli** | Caller | `aictl up/apply` transparently calls the kernel of this repository |
| **ai-guide-portal** | Caller | The portal triggers execution orchestration, and this repository is the execution core |
| **Deployed component** | Deployment object | This repository is the "assembler" of components such as gateway/sandbox |

---

## 2. Responsibilities List

| # | Responsibility | Type | Description |
|---|------|------|------|
| R1 | Plan consumption and verification | core | Read AssemblyPlan, pre-check resources/dependencies |
| R2 | Rendering Configuration | core | Plan -> Helm Values ​​/ Compose / Operator |
| R3 | incremental deployment | core | deployment/change differences only |
| R4 | rolling update | core | multi-copy rolling + probe keepalive |
| R5 | Canary upgrade | core | Those with greater impact will be cut after double-writing verification |
| R6 | rollback | core | declarative rollback (enabled=false replay) |
| R7 | Status Postback | core | Component Ready Status Postback Portal |

---

## 3. Core abstraction and interface

### 3.1 Execution model

```go
// Render product
type RenderOutput struct {
    Kind      string            // helm-values | compose | k8s-manifest
Artifacts map[string][]byte // file name -> YAML
}

//Execution result
type ApplyResult struct {
Component string // component name
    Action    string // add|reuse|remove|rolling-update
    Status    string // success|failed|in-progress
    Message   string
}

// Deploy target Port (SPI: CICD 1.0.0)
type Deployer interface {
    Render(ctx context.Context, plan AssemblyPlan, profile string) (RenderOutput, error)
    Apply(ctx context.Context, out RenderOutput) ([]ApplyResult, error)
    Rollback(ctx context.Context, component string, toVersion string) error
    Status(ctx context.Context, component string) ComponentStatus
}

type ComponentStatus struct {
    Name     string
    Ready    bool
    Version  string
    Replicas int
}

// CICD SPI（interface_versions.CICD = 1.0.0）
type CICDPort interface {
    Sync(ctx context.Context, manifest []byte) error
    RollbackTo(ctx context.Context, revision string) error
}
```

### 3.2 Layered architecture

| Layers | Packages | Responsibilities |
|----|-----|------|
| Domain layer | `domain/` | Deployer Port + RenderOutput/ApplyResult type |
| Application layer | `app/` | RenderAndApply / RollbackComponent use case |
| Adapter layer | `adapter/` | HelmAdapter / ComposeAdapter / ArgoCDAdapter |
| Infrastructure layer | `infrastructure/` | Configuration, Wire DI, K8s/Helm client |

---

## 4. Processing pipeline

```
portal/aictl -> ai-provisioning-engine
-> Preflight: Resource Quota + Dependency Graph + Conflict
-> [Failed] Block + Reason
-> [Pass] Render by profile (Helm Values/Compose/Operator)
-> Differential application: Added/Removed/change only
-> [Multiple copies] rolling update (maxSurge/maxUnavailable + probe)
-> [Big impact] Cut after double-write verification (canary)
-> [Removed] Declarative offline (enabled=false)
-> Detect Ready
-> [Not Ready] Retry/Timeout -> Rollback
-> [Ready] Status callback portal
-> Completed, zero downtime for original services
```

---

## 5. External adapter (SPI Adapter)

| SPI Port | Repository Role | External Components | Default/Alternate | Adapter |
|----------|----------|----------|-----------|---------|
| `CICD` (1.0.0) | Consumer | ArgoCD (optional) + Istio (optional, full only) | Alternatives/Alternatives | ArgoCDAdapter (GitOps sync/rollback) |
| `Cache` (1.0.0) | Consumer | Redis (core) | Default | Execution status/lock |
| `Tracing` (1.0.0) | Consumer | OTel (core) | Default | Deployment link trace |
| Deployment target | Direct driver | Kubernetes (Helm/Kubectl) / Docker Compose | Default | HelmAdapter / ComposeAdapter |

### Stage adaptation
- CICD (ArgoCD/Istio) is optional (only full file)
- starter/standard/advanced directly connected to Helm/Compose
- Full file goes to ArgoCD (multiple SPI implementations coexist)
- All deployment targets are isolated by Adapter, and there will be zero changes when switching

---

## 6. Key Design Decisions

| Decision | Content |
|------|------|
| Incremental principle | Only skip for Plan.Added deployment, Plan.Removed offline, and Plan.Reused |
| Rendering strategy | Select renderer by profile: starter=Compose; standard+/advanced/full=Helm/K8s |
| Rolling strategy | maxSurge:1 / maxUnavailable:0 + liveness/readiness probe |
| Canary upgrade | Double-write verification before cutover (Jo Chiat vector library Milvus<->Qdrant) |
| Rollback | Declarative: enabled, change back to false/old version replay Plan, ArgoCD/GitOps automatic rollback |
| Deployment namespace | `ai-system` (core) |
